      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "📌 ComfyUI Workflow Notes\n**Author:** Sharvin Suntoobacus  \n**YouTube Channel:** CodeCraftersCorner  \n**Patreon:** [Support on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/codecrafterscorner)\n\n---\n\n### ℹ️ About This Workflow\nThis workflow utilizes the **FireRed Image Edit 1.1** model to achieve precise character consistency from a single reference image. It allows users to generate a primary reference character and then seamlessly create multiple views (side, back, profile) or different poses while maintaining facial features and details. It includes support for the new **ComfyUI App Mode** for a streamlined, UI-driven experience.\n\n---\n\n### 🎥 Tutorial / Guide\n**[Watch on YouTube](https://youtu.be/8KMfL9EwTMA)**\n\n---\n\n### 📥 Model Links (for Local Users)\nDownload the following models to ensure the workflow functions correctly:\n\n**diffusion_models (UNET)**\n* [firered_image_edit_1.1_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/drbaph/FireRed-Image-Edit-1.1_ComfyUI_Quants/blob/main/firered_image_edit_1.1_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors) (or GGUF versions for lower VRAM)\n\n**loras**\n* [FireRed-Image-Edit-1.1-Lightning-8steps-v1.2.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/FireRedTeam/FireRed-Image-Edit-1.1-ComfyUI/blob/main/FireRed-Image-Edit-1.1-Lightning-8steps-v1.2.safetensors)\n\n**vae**\n* [qwen_image_vae.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/FireRedTeam/FireRed-Image-Edit-1.1-ComfyUI/blob/main/qwen_image_vae.safetensors)\n\nCLIP and VAE can be downloaded from the manager.\n\n---\n\n### 📂 Model Storage Location\nPlace the downloaded files into the following directories within your ComfyUI installation:\n\n📂 **ComfyUI/** \n\n├── 📂 **models/** \n\n│   ├── 📂 **diffusion_models/** \n\n│   │   └── firered_image_edit_1.1_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors  \n\n\n\n│   ├── 📂 **loras/** \n\n│   │   └── FireRed-Image-Edit-1.1-Lightning-8steps-v1.2.safetensors  \n\n\n│   └── 📂 **vae/** \n\n│       └── qwen_image_vae.safetensors  \n\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Notes\n* **App Mode:** Ensure your ComfyUI is updated to the latest version to access the \"App Mode\" beta feature.\n* **Hardware Requirements:** Recommended 12GB VRAM and 32GB RAM for FP8. If you experience Out of Memory (OOM) errors, switch the UNET node to a **GGUF** version (Q4 or Q5).\n* **Reference Images:** For best results, use a front-facing input image with a plain or simple background.\n* **Prompting:** The \"Subject\" prompt defines the character, while the \"Second View\" prompt should only describe the desired change (e.g., \"side profile\" or \"sitting\") rather than re-describing the whole image.\n\n**Credit:** Please credit Sharvin Suntoobacus and share YouTube Channel **Code Crafters Corner** when sharing this workflow.  \n**Support:** Your support on Patreon helps me continue creating these guides!\n\n🙏 **Thank you for your support!**"
      ],
